# Go service conventions

- Module: `github.com/PavaoZornija1/github-tracker`
- Binaries only under `cmd/api` and `cmd/worker`; shared code under `internal/`
- Plumb `context.Context` from handlers/workers to DB, Redis, Rabbit, and GitHub HTTP
- Use `slog` with request-id (HTTP) or job-id (worker) from context on every log line
- API errors: `{ "error": { "code": "...", "message": "..." } }` with correct status codes
- No inline imports — all imports at package top
- Exhaustive `switch` on enums/unions with `default` assigning to `never`-equivalent (`default: return fmt.Errorf("unhandled %v", x)`)
